    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>SWISS PHONE DEAL</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Elizabeth Olson</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Olson, Elizabeth</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Switzerland's leading phone company, Swisscom AG, will sell its satellite communications division to Verestar, unit of American Tower Operations (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Switzerland's leading phone company, Swisscom A.G., will sell its satellite communications division to Verestar, a unit of American Tower Operations, which provides communications services to cruise ships. No price was disclosed for the sale, which will include a satellite ground station. Swisscom, however, estimated that selling its 25-year-old satellite business would save about $58 million over the next decade and allow it to concentrate on undersea cables or other providers for its international traffic.</p>
        <p>Elizabeth Olson</p>
      </block>
